parameters: Excuse me, are you Mr. Kaigetsudou?
What do you want, kid? Do you need something from me?

Yes, my name is Karin. I've been sent by the owner of
Sumikuraya in Ueno to inquire about a painting that hasn't
been delivered yet.

Ah, the project that's past its deadline, right? I want to
paint, but unfortunately, my brush just isn't moving. We
artists have times when we're completely off, like a calm
sea. I'm sorry, but...

Even so, since you've taken on the job, you need to complete
it. Can't you find a way to get in the mood?

...Well now. Upon closer look, you're quite the beauty. You
have a dignified face and even at a young age, one can sense
a faint allure.

Is that so? Ah... thank you very much. You're making me
blush.

...Hmm, what do you say? I'll pay you a reward if you could
be a reference for my personal painting?
A reference for a painting? Me... really!?

Yes. I'm not inspired by the folding screen paintings for
the wealthy. I want to compete with my own art. What do you
say? I'll give you 2000 mon as a reward. Will you accept?

Could I... see the painting you've done, if it's not too
much trouble? (excited)

I'm sorry, but that's not possible. It's only outlined and
not finished yet. Once it's properly completed, I'll show it
to you.

Well well, thanks to Miss Karin, I'm feeling quite motivated
now. I'll deliver the folding screen painting to the client
in the next few days. Here's your reward. Please take it.

Thank you very much. Please make sure to deliver the folding
screen painting as promised.

...I'm sorry. This is all so sudden and I'm not prepared.
I'll come back to follow up on this later.
Kaigetsudou is fervently painting a picture.

Ah, Lady Karin. I am grateful for the other day. Thanks to
you, I am brimming with motivation.
Hello, Kaigetsudou-san. Is the painting finished?

Yes. It will be printed as a ukiyo-e next. Let me give you
one of the test prints. This is it.
Take one as a memento. I am thankful to you.

(Hehe. It's embarrassing to have a painting based on me...
I'll hang it at home...)
Kaigetsudou is fervently painting a picture.
